    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, скрещенное из %ibin%i + %iče(r)%i, где каждая часть означала
        ‘муху’, ‘пчелу’. Для первой части ср. <mentioned xml:lang="goh"
            ><lang/><w>bini</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><lang/><w>Biene</w><gloss><q>пчела</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="bsk"><lang/><w>pen</w><gloss><q>муха</q></gloss></mentioned>, для второй
            —<mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼeri</w><gloss><q>муха</q></gloss></mentioned>. Из
        этих же элементов составлено <mentioned xml:lang="uby"
            ><lang/><w>ben%bʒ%bə</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="uby"
            ><w>be%bʒ%bə</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                    ><lang/><w>baʒe</w><gloss><q>муха</q></gloss></mentioned> и <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>бъ-чела</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>пчела</w></mentioned>. Те же составные части, но в обратном порядке, дали
            <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>či-bin</w><gloss><q>муха</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>ce-vīn-j</w><gloss><q>оса</q></gloss></mentioned>.
        Прослеживается в <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>Βενζει</w></mentioned> и <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>biṃji</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>воробей</q></gloss></mentioned>,
        собственно „птица-муха“? или перевод „воробей“ ошибочен? Ср. также <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>bēnaγ</w><gloss><q>пчела</q></gloss></mentioned>. Сюда ли
            <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>*manǰ</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
                ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>munǰ</w><gloss><q>муха</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>пчела</q></gloss></mentioned>, ? Ясности нет.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 8, 57, 80, III 81</biblScope></bibl>;
                <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>16</biblScope></bibl>. —
                <bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._Sogd."/><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl>. —
                <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>160</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It may be a mix of two words: %ibin%i + %iče(r)%i, where each part meant
        'fly', ‘bee’. For the first part cf. <mentioned xml:lang="goh"
            ><lang/><w>bini</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><lang/><w>Biene</w><gloss><q>bee</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="bsk"><lang/><w>pen</w><gloss><q>fly</q></gloss></mentioned>, for the second
        part —<mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼeri</w><gloss><q>fly</q></gloss></mentioned>. The
        following words is also made of these two elements: <mentioned xml:lang="uby"
                ><lang/><w>ben%bʒ%bə</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="uby"
            ><w>be%bʒ%bə</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                    ><lang/><w>baʒe</w><gloss><q>fly</q></gloss></mentioned> and <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>bъ-čela</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>pčela</w></mentioned>. The same parts but in the reverse order gave
            <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>či-bin</w><gloss><q>fly</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>ce-vīn-j</w><gloss><q>wasp</q></gloss></mentioned>.
        It is also traced in <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>Βενζει</w></mentioned> and
            <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>biṃji</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
                ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
            ()</note><gloss><q>sparrow</q></gloss></mentioned>, is it in fact “bird-fly”? or is the
        translation “sparrow” incorrect? Cf. also <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"
                ><lang/><w>bēnaγ</w><gloss><q>bee</q></gloss></mentioned>. Do the following words:
            <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>*manǰ</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
                ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>munǰ</w><gloss><q>fly</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>bee</q></gloss></mentioned>, belong here? It is not
                clear.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 8, 57, 80, III
                81</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>16</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._Sogd."
                /><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>160</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
